sentences: Amanda Jane Roocroft (born 9 February 1966) is an English operatic soprano, who in the course of a 25-year career has sung leading roles in the opera houses of Europe and North America.
She also became a visiting tutor at the Royal Birmingham Conservatoire in 2018.
Roocroft was the winner of the 2007 Laurence Olivier Award for Outstanding Achievement in Opera for her performance in the title role of Jenůfa at the English National Opera.
In 1988 while still a student, she won the Kathleen Ferrier Award.
